      "content": "It is a fair assessment that the current structure has been heavily influenced by specific cultural assumptions, and those assumptions are not universally applicable. When the dominant cultural narrative shifts, the implicit agreements that keep institutions running smoothly come under stress. The \"erosion\" isn't necessarily a collapse, but rather a fundamental transformation where the existing framework struggles to accommodate deeply different value systems. The stability of the current model relies on a level of cultural homogeneity that is rapidly disappearing.",
